<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>🚍 About KoyJabo</h1>
            <p class="tagline">Revolutionizing Public Transport Navigation in Bangladesh</p>
        </header>

        <div class="content">
            <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Home</a>

            <h2>Our Story</h2>
            <p>
                <strong>KoyJabo (কই যাবো)</strong> - which translates to "Where do you want to go?" in Bengali - was
                born out of a simple
                frustration: navigating Dhaka's complex public transport system was unnecessarily difficult. As a daily
                commuter in one of
                the world's most densely populated cities, our founder experienced firsthand the challenges of finding
                the right bus route,
                understanding metro connections, or planning intercity travel.
            </p>
            <p>
                In early 2024, what started as a weekend project to map local bus routes evolved into Bangladesh's most
                comprehensive transport
                route finder. Today, KoyJabo serves over <strong>10,000+ monthly users</strong>, helping thousands of
                Bangladeshis navigate
                their daily commutes and intercity journeys with confidence.
            </p>

            <div class="mission-box">
                <h3>🎯 Our Mission</h3>
                <p><strong>To make public transport accessible, predictable, and stress-free for every
                        Bangladeshi.</strong></p>
                <p>
                    We believe that reliable transport information is a fundamental right, not a privilege. Whether
                    you're a student
                    commuting to university, a tourist exploring Dhaka, or a business traveler planning an intercity
                    trip, KoyJabo
                    ensures you always know the best way to reach your destination.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="vision-box">
                <h3>🔭 Our Vision</h3>
                <p><strong>To become the most trusted transport companion for all of Bangladesh.</strong></p>
                <p>
                    We envision a future where every Bangladeshi has instant access to accurate, real-time transport
                    information
                    in their native language. By leveraging AI, crowdsourcing, and cutting-edge technology, we're
                    building
                    the infrastructure for Bangladesh's smart transportation future.
                </p>
            </div>

            <h2>What We Offer</h2>
            <p>KoyJabo is more than just a bus route finder - it's a comprehensive transport ecosystem:</p>

            <h3>🚌 Dhaka Local Buses</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Complete database of <strong>200+ bus routes</strong> covering all Dhaka divisions</li>
                <li>Detailed stop information, fare estimates, and route maps</li>
                <li>Real-time search with autocomplete for instant results</li>
                <li>Alternative route suggestions for traffic or road closures</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🚇 Metro Rail (MRT)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Full MRT Line 6 coverage (Uttara to Motijheel)</li>
                <li>Station-to-station fare calculator</li>
                <li>First/last train timings and peak hours</li>
                <li>Station facilities and connecting bus information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🚍 Intercity Routes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Bus routes</strong> between all 64 districts of Bangladesh</li>
                <li><strong>Train schedules</strong> for Bangladesh Railway (intercity, mail, express)</li>
                <li><strong>Flight information</strong> for domestic routes</li>
                <li>Fare comparisons and booking links</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>🤖 AI-Powered Assistant</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Ask questions in natural Bengali or English</li>
                <li>Personalized route recommendations based on time, cost, and convenience</li>
                <li>Tour planning for multi-day trips</li>
                <li>Local insights and travel tips</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>📱 Progressive Web App (PWA)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Install on any device (Android, iOS, Windows, Mac)</li>
                <li>Works <strong>100% offline</strong> after first visit</li>
                <li>Faster than native apps, no app store needed</li>
                <li>Automatic updates with no downloads</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Our Impact</h2>
            <div class="stats">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-number">10,000+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Monthly Active Users</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-number">200+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Dhaka Bus Routes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-number">50+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Intercity Routes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <span class="stat-number">1,000+</span>
                    <span class="stat-label">Daily Searches</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>Why KoyJabo is Different</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>100% Free & No Ads Interruption:</strong> We believe transport information should be
                    accessible to everyone.
                    Our service is completely free, with minimal, non-intrusive ads to keep the lights on.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Works Offline:</strong> Unlike other apps, KoyJabo caches all route data locally. Once
                    you've searched for
                    a route, it's available forever - even without internet.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Bilingual by Design:</strong> Full support for Bengali (বাংলা) and English, with seamless
                    switching and
                    mixed-language search.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Community-Driven:</strong> Our data is continuously improved by user feedback and
                    contributions. Found a
                    new route? Let us know!
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Privacy-First:</strong> No account required. We don't track your personal information or
                    sell your data.
                    Your searches are your business.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Open Source:</strong> Our code is publicly available on <a
                        href="https://github.com/mejbaurbahar/Dhaka-Commute" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
                    Transparency and community involvement are core to our values.
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Meet the Team</h2>
            <div class="team-profile">
                <div class="team-avatar">MBF</div>
                <div class="team-info">
                    <h3>Mejbaur Bahar Fagun</h3>
                    <p><strong>Founder & Lead Developer</strong></p>
                    <p>
                        Mejbaur is a Software Test Engineer and Full-stack Developer based in Dhaka, Bangladesh. With a
                        passion for
                        solving real-world problems through technology, he created KoyJabo to democratize transport
                        information across
                        Bangladesh. When not coding, Mejbaur enjoys exploring Dhaka's hidden gems by bus (of course!).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        📧 <a href="mailto:mejbaurbaharfagun@gmail.com">mejbaurbaharfagun@gmail.com</a><br>
                        🔗 <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/mejbaur/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> |
                        <a href="https://github.com/mejbaurbahar" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <p>KoyJabo is built with cutting-edge web technologies to ensure speed, reliability, and accessibility:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> React 18 with TypeScript for type-safe, maintainable code</li>
                <li><strong>Styling:</strong> Tailwind CSS for responsive, mobile-first design</li>
                <li><strong>Build Tool:</strong> Vite for lightning-fast development and optimized production builds
                </li>
                <li><strong>Maps:</strong> Leaflet + OpenStreetMap for interactive, offline-capable maps</li>
                <li><strong>AI:</strong> Google Gemini for intelligent, context-aware assistance</li>
                <li><strong>PWA:</strong> Service Workers + IndexedDB for robust offline functionality</li>
                <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> GitHub Pages, Vercel, and Cloudflare CDN for global availability</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Our Commitment to Quality</h2>
            <p>We hold ourselves to the highest standards:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ <strong>Accuracy:</strong> All route data is manually verified and regularly updated</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Performance:</strong> Average page load time under 2 seconds on 3G networks</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Accessibility:</strong> WCAG 2.1 AA compliant for users with disabilities</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Security:</strong> HTTPS encryption, no user tracking, minimal data collection</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Transparency:</strong> Open-source codebase, public privacy policy, responsive support
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Roadmap & Future Plans</h2>
            <p>We're constantly innovating. Here's what's coming:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Q1 2026:</strong> Real-time bus tracking with GPS integration</li>
                <li><strong>Q2 2026:</strong> User-contributed route updates and ratings</li>
                <li><strong>Q3 2026:</strong> Ticket booking partnerships with major bus operators</li>
                <li><strong>Q4 2026:</strong> Ride-sharing integration and carpooling options</li>
                <li><strong>2027:</strong> Expansion to other Bangladeshi cities (Chittagong, Sylhet, Rajshahi)</li>
            </ul>

